Dort liess er sich stark durch das seit den späten 60ern entstandenen Graffiti-Writing inspirieren und studierte an der School of Visual Arts. Zu seinen Markenzeichen gehört das sogenannte "Radiant Baby" (ein Baby mit Strahlenkreuz). Dem europäischen Publikum bekannt wurde Keith Haring insbesondere durch seine Graffitis an der Berliner Mauer. -- This book documents the work of the famous graffiti artist Keith Haring. Other questions? Keith Haring (born 4th Mai 1968 in Reading, USA, died in February 1990 in New York) dropped out of his degree course as a commercial graphic designer in Pittsburgh 1978 and moved to New York. There, he got strongly influenced by graffiti writing that had been on the rise since the 60ies and studied at the School of Visual Arts. One of his trademarks is his so-called "Radiant Baby". description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 9.--/EUR 7.-- Marker: Paint Marker. Tip (Spitze): 15 mm Spitze. Farbe: Entspricht der Farbzusammensetzung der 94er Mtn-Sprühdose. Eigenschaften: Unglaubliche Deckkraft, leuchtende Farben mit Satinglanz-Finish. Geegnet für Metall, Stein, Glas, Kunststoffe, Leder, Papier, Pappe, Holz, Textil, Terracotta etc. Extras: Schnell nachfüllbar dank Schraubverschluss am unteren Ende. Die beiden Graffitikünstler "Moockie" und "Kapi" planten ursprünglich 1993 gemeinsam mit dem Farbenhersteller "Felton" und dem Manager eines Sprühdosenherstellers, Jordi Rubio, das Projekt "Montana". Nach einigen Querelen, kam 1994 schliesslich die erste Dose auf den Markt. Zuerst die "Hardcore", 2001 die "Alien". Die Marke wurde schnell beliebt und Barcelona (nicht zuletzt wegen deren damals sehr liberalen Richtlinien in Bezug auf Graffiti Art) zum "Melting-Point" der europäischen Sprayerszene. Ende 1995 wurde die Dose in weitere Länder exportiert und damit begannen auch die Probleme. Die deutsche Firma "L&G" übernahm 1997 exklusiv die Vertriebsrechte für Deutschaland. Später kam es zu Differenzen und einem jahrelangen Rechtsstreit zwischen „Montana Spanien“ und "Monatana Deutschland", in welchen auch der amerikanische Autolackhersteller "Dupli Color" und die Schweizer Firma "Farbo" umstrittene Rollen spielten. Schliesslich kam es zum Bruch zwischen "Montana Spanien" und "Montana Deutschland". Letztere brachten ab 2001 mehrere eigene Dosen wie "Montana Gold" und "Montana Black" auf den Markt, während "Mtn Barcelona" zuletzt mit der "94" und der "Hardcore 2" den Markt revolutionierte. "Mtn" the original! -- Marker: Paint Marker. Tip: 15 mm tip Paint: Similar in formula to the 94 Mtn spray can. Characteristics: Incredible coverage, bright colours with satin gloss finish. For metal, stone, glass, plastics, leather, paper, cardboard, wood textiles, terracotta etc. Extras: Easy to refill thanks to the screw cap at the bottom. Originally, it was the two graffiti artists "Moockie" and "Kapi" who planned the project "Montana" together with paint producer "Felton" and Jordi Rubio, a manager at a can producer in 1993. After quite some quarrelling, the first can came to the market in 1994. First the "Hardcore", then the "Alien" in 2001. The brand instantly became popular and Barcelona a melting pot for the European graffiti scene (also because of the then very liberal graffiti art policies). By the end of 1995, the can was also exported to other countries – and that’s when the problems started. In 1997, the German company "L&G" got the exclusive distribution rights for Germany. Later, differences became apparent and a years long legal battle between Montana Spain and Montana Germany ensued, in which the American car finish producer "Dupli Color" and the Swiss company "Farbo" played dubious roles. Eventually, "Montana Spain" and "Montana Germany" broke off their relations. After 2001, the latter brought several own cans to the market, such as "Montana Gold" and "Montana Black". Meanwhile, "Mtn Bercelona" went on to revolutionize the market once again, first with the "94" and recently with the "Hardcore 2". Mtn, the original! File under: Tag marker

Deren Umgang mit dem Tod wirkt auf westliche Kulturen oft befremdlich, da der Tod nicht tabuisiert wird. Das Spektrum der Darstellungen reicht von barocker Pracht über makaber-düstere Leichname bis zu grinsenden Gerippen in bunter Bemalung. Dieses grossartige Buch erlaubt einen Blick auf dieses indigene Brauchtum, das 2003 von der UNESCO in die Liste der „Meisterwerke des mündlichen und immateriellen Erbes der Menschheit“ aufgenommen wurde. -- An explosive collection of amazing contemporary lowbrow and kustom art inspired by the Mexican Day of the Dead. Showcasing 47 international artists from the USA, Mexico, Europe and Japan. Among those featured are Sergio Mora, Rhode Montijo, DR. Lakra, Laurie Lipton, Brian Ewing, Fudemae and Jose Quintero. Terrifying and intriguing in equal measure, and covering the origins of this amazingly vibrant genre, The Day of the Dead is an eye-watering feast of visual inspiration. File under: Korero, Death, Skulls, Placebo

name: Monster Kolor - Paint Marker
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 7.--/EUR 6.-- "Monster Kolor" - I'ts the premium marker for your toys! "Monster Kolor" von Matt Walker (Dead Presidents Design) aus New England/USA, ist eine schnelltrocknende Farbe, welche sich besonders in Kreisen von Kaiju- und Toy-Designern grosser Beliebtheit erfreut. Die Nummer 1 im Bereich des Toy-Designs! Zu den Spezialitäten dieser Kultfarbe des ehemaligen Autolackierers Walker, gehören die knalligen Matallic- und lichtdurchlässigen Kunstharzlacke ("C-thru"). Einige Farben von "Monster Kolor" eignen sich auch für "Airbrush". Marker Farbe: Schnelltrocknende Tinte aus den USA Spitze: Rundspitze (2mm) Eigenschaften: Eignet sich besonders für Materialien wie Kunststoff, Plastik, Vinyl, Gummi, PVC und Metal. Vorteil: Besonders geeignet für Custom Toys. -- "Monster Kolor" by automobile pinstriper Matt Walker (Dead Presidents Design) from New England/USA is a custom paint system for toys of all kinds. I'ts the premium paint for your toys! Fast drying, solvent based ink-marker with a round-tip (2mm). Specifically made for use on toys and on materials like: PVC, plastic, vinyl, resin, rubber, metal etc. File under: Marker, Do-it-yourself, Custom Toys, Character Design

name: Charles Fréger - Wilder Mann
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 45.--/EUR 35.-- A ritual masquerade like character design by the French photographer Charles Fréger! The rituals are centuries old and celebrate the seasonal cycle, fertility, life, and death. People literally put themselves into the skin of the "savage," in masquerades that stretch back centuries. By becoming a bear, a goat, a stag, a wild boar, a man of straw, a devil, or a monster with jaws of steel, these people celebrate the cycle of life and seasons. The costumes amaze with their extraordinary diversity and prodigious beauty. Work on this project took leading French photographer Charles Fréger to eighteen European countries in search of the mythological figure of the "Wild Man". Language: German File under: Kehrer, Photography, Character Design

name: Artur Beifuss & Francesco Trivini Bellini - Branding Terror
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 50.--/EUR 39.-- The logotypes and iconography of insurgent groups and terrorist organizations around the world! Terrorist groups are no different from other organizations in their use of branding to promote their ideas. The branding they employ may contain complex systems of meaning and emotion. "Branding Terror" is the first comprehensive survey of the visual identity of the world’s major terrorist organizations, from "Al-Qaeda" to the "Tamil Tigers". Each of the 60-plus entries contains a concise description of the group’s ideology and the group’s branding – the symbolism, colours and typography of its logo and flag – is then analysed in detail. "Branding Terror" does not seek to make any political statements; rather, it offers insight into an understudied area of counter-intelligence, and provides an original and provocative source of inspiration for graphic designers. A design book like a bomb! File under: Graphic Design, Logo, Merrell

name: KCBR - Live Life Like
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 69.--/EUR 52.-- "Live Life Like" is a radical contemporary document about one of the most active graffiti-crews from Zurich/Switzerland: KCBR! In the last few years the sprayers of KCBR worked intensively in Zurich/Switzerland: You can see their tags in each corner in the city (on roofs, facades, trains and, and, and, everywhere)! Now, you can see their tags also in an art book! Do you like them? We do, then: Support your local vandals - sometimes! With a Foreword by Daniel "Göldin" Ryser (Das Magazin). KCBR is a anonymous graffiti-crew from Zurich/Switzerland. SYLV! File under: Graffiti, Street Art, Tags, Swiss Design, Patrick Frey

name: Paul Koudounaris - The Empire of Death
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 63.--/EUR 48.-- A picture album about decorated charnels, tombs and chapels! Sightseeing in a different way! Der Umgang mit dem Tod ist weltweit so unterschiedlich, wie die Völker und Kulturen unterschiedlich sind. Dieses Buch führt Interessierte an ganz unterschiedliche, kulturell wertvolle Grabstätten in über 20 Ländern (selbst einige Orte in der Schweiz wurden aufgeführt!). Sozusagen ein Reiseführer der anderen Art! -- Beginning in the early modern period and continuing to the 19th century, elaborately decorated charnels, tombs and chapels were constructed with the focus on human bone. This riveting book takes the reader on a tour of these macabre masterpieces with specially taken, arresting photographs and a commentary researched from a multitude of sources. It's a momento mori for our age. Paul Koudounaris has a doctorate in Art History from the University of California, Los Angeles, and has written widely on European ossuaries and charnel houses for both academic and popular journals. He visited and photographed over seventy sites containing human bones in nearly twenty countries in the course of writing this book. File under: Thames & Hudson, Death, Skulls, Placebo

name: Peter Bolz & Viola König - Indianische Moderne (Kunst aus Nordamerika)
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 40.--/EUR 31.-- If you like street art from artists like "Tika" or "Iuna Tinta"? You will love this book also! Because: Maybe they are affected by art of Native Americans? Art has a very special place in the culture of Native Americans. Most art was created as a symbol, such as a bear, walrus, eagle, or people. In this book from the exhibition "Indianische Moderne - Kunst aus Nordamerika" at "Ethnologisches Museum" in Berlin/Germany, you will learn all about interesting tribal patterns, unbelievable colorful drawnings, wooden sculptures like Totem poles from the "First Nations". Language: Deutsch File under: Art

name: Suck UK - Grime Writer
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 14.--/EUR 10.-- The "Grime Writer" helps you leave your mark wherever you find muck! No ink, no paint, just cleaning solvents! Grime Writer is a special chunky marker pen that can be filled with cleaning solution, and used to create art on a canvas of filth. Use it to tag your dirty vehicles, windows, walls or to transform dirt into artistic expression. Please help us, to promote the phenomenon of reverse graffiti with this soap-marker! description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 17.--/EUR 13.-- Büro Destruct - Kinderfragebuch (Astronaut) The book contains 333 Questions (Language: German) for kids at the age of 7 to 99 years, 29 entertaining tasks humorously illustrated with typical BD characters. „Und wie war es in der Schule?“ - oft erhält man auf die üblichen Fragen nichts als ein kindliches Schulterzucken. Dazu gibt es auf vielen Seiten spannende Aufgaben und lustige Spiele, auf anderen Platz, um Erinnerungen aufzuschreiben oder Bilder einzukleben. Ein Buch für neugierige Eltern, die wissen wollen, was wirklich in ihren Kindern vorgeht und die Welt wieder mal durch Kinderaugen sehen wollen. Vor allem aber ein Buch für Kinder! Illustrations, typography and design of the „Kinderfragebuch“ kids book by Lopetz (Büro Destruct), written by Mikael Krogerus & Roman Tschäppeler, both authors of the „Decision Book“. name: Adrian Frutiger - Der Mensch und seine Zeichen
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 42.--/EUR 32.-- Frutigers Book "Der Mensch und seine Zeichen" (man and his signs) published in 1978 is considered a standard works for sign-theory in its practical graphic application as for instance in the design of a logo. This excellent book is a must for any who want to get an introductory but still thorough look into the phenomenon of signs and symbols in general and the the development of fonts in particular! Language/Sprache: German/Deutsch Adrian Frutiger was born on May 24th 1928 in Interlaken, Berner Oberland/Switzerland and is among the most important font designers of the 20th century. Among his best known fonts are the serif-less "Linear-Antiqua Univers" and the "Roissy" which was designed for the Parisian airport Charles de Gaulle, an early form of the “Frutiger” (which adorns all traffic signs in Switzerland). His "OCR-B“, optimized for machine-readability was made the ISO-Standard in 1973. These days Adrian Frutiger lives in Bremgarten near Berne/Switzerland. name: Alan Aldridge - The Man with the Kaleidoscope Eyes
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 52.--/EUR 39.-- Dieses Buch zeigt eine gute Auswahl fantasievoller Entwürfe und farbenprächtiger Bilder des Grafikers Alan Aldridge, der in durch seine visuellen Auftragsarbeiten für The Beatles in den 60ern sozusagen Musikgeschichte schrieb. Seine oft surreal anmutenden Zeichnungen trafen der Nerv einer ganzen Generation und dürften auch Künstler wie Jim Woodring oder Mark Ryden beeinflusst haben. Grafik wie ein LSD-Trip! Der Grafiker und Illustrator Alan Aldridge wurde 1943 in London (England) geboren und wurde weltweit bekannt durch seine Auftragsarbeiten für The Beatles. Unter anderem stammt von ihm das Logo für deren Label "Apple" (nicht zu verwechseln mit dem amerikanischen Hersteller von Apple-Mac-Computern). Das Logo zeigt einen grünen Plattenspieler in Form eines Apfels. Aldridge lebt heute in Los Angeles (USA) und zeichnet sich desweiteren verantwortlich für viele Plattencovers anderer bekannter Bands oder Filmplakate (u.a. für Andy Warhol’s "Chelsea Girls"). Eine Grafik-Legende! -- This book presents a good selection of creative layouts and colourful pictures of the graphic designer Alan Aldridge, who wrote music history in the 1960s with his contract work for The Beatles. His drawings often bear a surreal touch, thus struck a cord with a whole generation and have influenced artists such as Jim Woodring or Mark Ryden. Graphic design as an LSD-trip! The graphic designer and illustrator Alan Aldridge was born 1943 in London (England) and became world famous with his contract work for The Beatles. Among others, he created the logo for their label "Apple" (not to be confused with the American producer of Apple-Mac-computers). The Logo shows a green record player in the shape of an apple. Today, Aldridge lives in Los Angeles (USA) and is responsible for many record covers of other well-known bands or movie posters (such as Andy Warhol’s "Chelsea Girls"). A legend in graphic design! File under: Grafik, Graphic Design, Psychedelic Art

description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 42.--/EUR 31.-- Die Werke in "Awful Resilient" (Pic 1) von Alex Pardee zeigen oft monsterähnliche Gestalten mit entstellten Gliedmassen, was freilich völlig im Gegensatz zu seinen schrill-bunten Farbkombinationen steht. Mystisch schön! Alex Pardee wurde 1976 in Antioch (USA) geboren und gehört zum Designerkollektiv "Zerofriends". -- The work of "Awful Resilient" (PIC 1) by Alex Pardee often centres around monster-like creatures with deformed extremities – quite in contrast to the shrill-checkered colour combinations. Mystically beautiful! Alex Pardee was born 1976 in Antioch (USA) and belongs to the design collective "Zerofriends". In our Büro-Discount assortment you will find also the publication "Awful Homesick" (Pic 2) by Alex Pardee. Please order now with the drop down menu! File under: Placebo, Art, Illustration

name: Alex Steinweiss - The Inventor of the Modern Album Cover
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 74.--/EUR 55.-- Im Laufe von dreissig Jahren schuf Steinweiss Tausende von Originalentwürfen für Schallplattencover aus den Bereichen Jazz, Klassik und Popmusik. Freilich gehörte zu seiner Arbeit als Grafiker auch die Kreation von Logos und weiterführendem Werbematerial. Sogar eine eigene Schrift (die "Steinweiss Scrawl") entwarf der Plattencover-Pionier und beeinflusste damit gleich mehrere Generationen von Grafikdesignern. Diese hervorragende Retrospektive zeigt aber nicht nur viele seiner Plattencover und bisher unveröffentlichte Skizzen, sondern auch rein künstlerische Arbeiten aus seinem reichhaltigen Nachlass. Natürlich ein Muss für jeden Grafiker! Der Grafiker Alex Steinweiss (geboren am 24. März 1917 in New York/USA, gestorben am 17. Juli 2011 in Sarasota/USA) gilt als Erfinder des Plattencovers. 1940 hatte Steinweiss als Art Director des Labels "Columbia Records" die grosse Eingebung, die bis dato blanken Plattenhüllen ansprechender zu gestalten. Im Februar 1940 erschien die erste Schallplatte ("Smash song hits" by Rodgers & Hart) mit einem Design auf der Hülle. Darauf stiegen die Verkaufszahlen von Schallplatten signifikant an. 1972 zog sich Steinweiss aus dem Geschäft als Gestalter von Plattenhüllen zurück. Der engen Verbindung von Musik und Motiv blieb er indes dennoch treu. Unter dem Künstlernamen Piedra Blanca (die spanischen Begriffe für "Stein" und "Weiss") begann er, Gemäldeserien nach den Meisterwerken berühmter Komponisten zu malen. -- In over thirty years the pioneering sleeve designer Steinweiss created original artwork for thousands for record covers in jazz, classic and pop music. His work also encompassed the creation of logos and further advertising materials. Steinweiss even developed his own font ("Steinweiss Scrawl") and with it influenced several generations of graphic designers. This outstanding retrospective doesn’t only show many of his record covers and previously unreleased sketches, but also purely artistic work from his rich legacy. A must have for every graphic designer! The graphic designer Alex Steinweiss (born 24th March 1917 in New York, died July 17th 2011 in Sarasota) is regarded as the inventor of the record cover. In a stroke of genius, the then art director of "Columbia Records", Steinweiss made the hitherto blank record sleeves more attractive. In February 1940 the first record with a designed sleeve was released ("Smash Song Hits" by Rodgers & Hart). In the aftermath, record sales rose significantly. In 1972 Steinweiss retired from sleeve design, but remained true to linking music and motive. Under the alias of Piedra Blanca (his name in Spanish) he created a series of paintings based on masterpieces of famed composers. File under: Grafik, Grphic Design

The Dutch photographer and video-clip director Anton Corbijn is without doubt one of the best known and most visible artists of his trade. His name is tightly linked with the success of Depeche Mode whose visuals bear his mark more clearly than anyone else’s. It was high time that the series "The Work of Director“ honoured him with a retrospective! On the disc can be found, among others, works for Nirvana, U2, his neighbour Herbert Grönemeyer and of course several videos he made for Depeche Mode. Further playing tips are: "Liar“ for Henry Rollins and "Front by Front“ for Front 242. Then again, every single work by Anton Corbijn really is a true feast for the eyes! description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 31.--/EUR 24.-- Die Styles des international renommierten Schweizer Street-Art-Künstlers Ata Bozaci (Toast) sind so unterschiedlich wie Begegnungen auf der Strasse selbst. Dieses Buch zeigt eine umfangreiche Retrospektive seiner Arbeiten seit seiner Jugendzeit in den 90ern bis heute. Ein Must-have insbesondere für jeden Kenner der Schweizer Graffiti-Szene! Ata Bozaci (Toast One, Atalier, Pyro Chimps) ist ein Berner Graffitikünstler mit Jahrgang 1974. Gemeinsam mit dem 2010 verstorbenen "Dare" (Rest in Peace, Sigi) gehört er zewifellos zu den bekanntesten Graffitikünstler der Schweiz. Der Burgdorfer Bozaci besuchte die Grafikfachklasse der Hochschule für Gestaltung und Kunst Bern, sprüht bereits seit den frühen 90ern und leitete lange Jahre sein Grafikstudio "Atalier". 2004 stellte er im Büro Discount Zürich aus, später wurde eine Sprühdosenfarbe der Marke Belton Molotow (Toast, Signal Schwarz) nach ihm benannt und 2007 wurde er von Gunter Sachs, seines Zeichens passionierter Kunstsammler und -Förderer, gebeten, dessen private Residenz am Wörthersee mit 10 Wandgemälden neu zu gestalten (eine Ehre die unter anderem auch Andy Warhol zukam). Heute lebt und arbeitet Ata Bozaci (Toast) in Zürich/Schweiz. File under: Publikat, Street Art, Graffiti, Writing, Graphic Design, Character Design, Logos, Swiss, Art

Sometimes he raises the admonishing moral finger. But mostly he is squeezing the trigger of a can of spray paint. And that is good. There’s no doubt: This book is a must and no art-book collection would be complete without it! Nach einigen Querelen, kam 1994 schliesslich die erste Dose auf den Markt. Zuerst die "Hardcore", 2001 die "Alien". Die Marke wurde schnell beliebt und Barcelona (nicht zuletzt wegen deren damals sehr liberalen Richtlinien in Bezug auf Graffiti Art) zum "Melting-Point" der europäischen Sprayerszene. Ende 1995 wurde die Dose in weitere Länder exportiert und damit begannen auch die Probleme. Die deutsche Firma "L&G" übernahm 1997 exklusiv die Vertriebsrechte für Deutschaland. Später kam es zu Differenzen und einem jahrelangen Rechtsstreit zwischen „Montana Spanien“ und "Monatana Deutschland", in welchen auch der amerikanische Autolackhersteller "Dupli Color" und die Schweizer Firma "Farbo" umstrittene Rollen spielten. Schliesslich kam es zum Bruch zwischen "Montana Spanien" und "Montana Deutschland". Letztere brachten ab 2001 mehrere eigene Dosen wie "Montana Gold" und "Montana Black" auf den Markt, während "Mtn Barcelona" zuletzt mit der "94" und der "Hardcore 2" den Markt revolutionierte. Originally, it was the two graffiti artists "Moockie" and "Kapi" who planned the project "Montana" together with paint producer "Felton" and Jordi Rubio, a manager at a can producer in 1993. After quite some quarrelling, the first can came to the market in 1994. First the "Hardcore", then the "Alien" in 2001. The brand instantly became popular and Barcelona a melting pot for the European graffiti scene (also because of the then very liberal graffiti art policies). By the end of 1995, the can was also exported to other countries – and that’s when the problems started. In 1997, the German company "L&G" got the exclusive distribution rights for Germany. Later, differences became apparent and a years long legal battle between Montana Spain and Montana Germany ensued, in which the American car finish producer "Dupli Color" and the Swiss company "Farbo" played dubious roles. Eventually, "Montana Spain" and "Montana Germany" broke off their relations. After 2001, the latter brought several own cans to the market, such as "Montana Gold" and "Montana Black". Meanwhile, "Mtn Bercelona" went on to revolutionize the market once again, first with the "94" and recently with the "Hardcore 2". Mtn, the original! File under: Nachfülltinte, Montana,

Zu seinen bekanntesten Charakteren gehören Fritz the Cat und Mr. Natural, beide zeichnen sich durch üppige Fleischeslust aus. Während sich Crumb für das Cover von Janis Joplin's "Cheap Thrills" und die Schrift ihres Albums "I Got Dem Ol' Kozmic Blues Again Mama" verantwortlich zeichnet, lehnte er auch immer wieder viele kommerzielle Aufträge ab (beispielsweise einen Auftrag der Rolling Stones). Robert Crumb lebt und arbeitet in Frankreich. -- Fritz the Cat is a comic by Robert Crumb, made into a cartoon movie in 1972 by Ralph Bakshi. Because of Fritz’s many sexual escapades, the film was a worldwide scandal and was only certified for adults. Crumb himself didn’t like the movie either. So he had Fritz the Cat later battered to death by a female ostrich using an ice pick. Weird! Robert Crumb was born on August 30, 1943 in Philadelphia (USA) and is said to be one of the most significant American underground comic artists. Two of his best-known characters are Fritz the Cat and Mr. Natural, both are rife with carnal desire. While Crumb did design the cover of Janis Joplin's "Cheap Thrills" and the font for the album "I Got Dem Ol' Kozmic Blues Again Mama", he declined many commercial assignments, for example one from the Rolling Stones. Robert Crumb lives and works in France. File under: Comics, Cartoons, Lowbrow

With his sexually motivated photo series, particularly those for fashion label Sisley, he caused quite a stir and wide-spread blushing and at the same time created the so-called „Porn Chic“. name: Trevor Brown - My Alphabet (signed)
description: Approximate price/umgerechnet in USD 85.--/EUR 65.-- It's his alphabet: The girls, children and dolls by Trevor Brown are no longer cute. They were flayed, beaten and raped! Trevor Brown’s images shock and outrage through their obtrusive hyper-realism. Violence, war, obscenity and fascism are his themes. But to therefore consider Brown a polemic provocateur would be too simple. He mercilessly confronts us with our image in the mirror, plays with our emotions, our deepest fears and our vulnerability. But isn’t it often our own fascination with the terrible which he triggers with his images and which scares us even more? Decide for yourself! Trevor Brown was born in England and now lives and works in Japan. Formally and by content his works are reminiscent of the works of surrealist Hans Bellmer or neoromanticist Gottfried Helnwein. His affinity with Young Brit Art by artists like Damien Hirst or the brothers Jake and Dinos Chapman is highly visible too. There are also influences from kitsch-art from Jeff Koons, pop art and Japanese Manga comics à la Junko Mizuno to detect.
